---
description: apply to any files in the components folder
globs: components/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
- Create purpose-specific components that do one thing well
- Split large components into smaller ones if they exceed 150 lines
- Apply appropriate React Native Reusables when available
- [react-native-reusables.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/react-native-reusables.mdc)
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces for all component props
- Add appropriate accessibility attributes (accessible, accessibilityLabel)
- Create component test files alongside component files when needed
- Export components individually from barrel files (index.ts)
- Implement appropriate loading and error states for all components
- Leverage React.memo() for performance optimization when appropriate
- Never modify components in the ui/ directory directly; create wrappers instead
